 <item> <title>National Student Loan Cohort Default Rate Declines Steadily</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/national-student-loan-cohort-default-rate-declines-steadily</link>
 <description>The U.S. Department of Education today announced that the three-year federal student loan cohort default rate dropped from 11.8 percent to 11.3 percent for students who entered repayment between fiscal years 2012 and 2013. The trend has moved downward since FY 2010, when the cohort default rate stood at 14.7 percent.</description>
