 <item> <title>First Official Three-Year Student Loan Default Rates Published</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/first-official-three-year-student-loan-default-rates-published</link>
 <description>The U.S. Department of Education today released official FY 2010 two-year and official FY 2009 three-year federal student loan cohort default rates. This is the first time the Department has issued an official three-year rate, which was 13.4 percent nationally for the FY 2009 cohort, a slight decrease from the trial three-year rate of 13.8 percent for the FY 2008 cohort.</description>
