 <item> <title>Student Loan Default Rates Increase</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/student-loan-default-rates-increase-0</link>
 <description> U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that the FY 2008 national cohort default rate is 7.0 percent, up from the FY 2007 rate of 6.7 percent. The default rates increased from 5.9 to 6 percent for public institutions, from 3.7 to 4 percent for private institutions, and from 11 to 11.6 percent for for-profit schools. </description>
